
LAboratory Document Indexer (LADI)

Martin Krzywinski*, Stephen Montgomery, Steven Jones
Genome Sciences Center (www.bcgsc.ca)
Vancouver BC Canada

* martink@bcgsc.ca

For documentation and updates see http://mkweb.bcgsc.ca/ladi

Quick Install

0. install GDS on GDSHOST (http://desktop.google.com)
1. untar ladi-x.xx.
2. copy contents of bin/ to GDSHOST (Windows machine running GDS)
3. start server.pl on GDSHOST
4. copy contents of web/ to GDSWEBHOST (web server providing interface to LADI)
5. configure LADI (web/etc/ladi.conf) including GDS IP address, site ID and repository file mapping






